Body:
I am trying to take a payload from an IoT sensor (I can edit the embedded code in the sensor) and put it in a DynamoDB in AWS.

This is what I get:

Payload: { "state" : { "M" : { "reported" : { "M" : { "Watt" : { "N" : "999" } } }
column9:
"SensorNo" : { "N" : "1" } } } }"

In the DynamoDB I get proper values written as SensorNo: 1
column10:
but Watt is set to 1538330043128.

I have tried to configure them as both Number and String
column11:
but with same result.

Any suggestions what might cause this? I want it to write 999 as the Payload say.

"

Body: The 1538330043128 numbers looks like an Epoch millisecond timestamp (September 30, 2018 5:54:03 UTC). Is the code that writes to DynamoDB putting the wrong value as the Watt?
Thank you Tom! You were absolutely correct! It sure was an Epoch timestamp, and the issue was my Hash Key formatting. Now it works! Thanks.
